      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey so i just finished changing the brake pads on my 2018 camry but now when i pull into a stop or drive slow i'm hearing this really high pitched squeal coming from the front end. not sure if i did something wrong with the installation or if something is stuck. could be the sensor or maybe a caliper? what should i check first?",
