      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A high-pitched squeal after a brake job often points to a few common culprits, and the first thing to check is the brake pads themselves. Inspect the new pads to ensure they are seated correctly and that no metal shavings or debris are stuck between the pad and the rotor. If the pads look fine, then inspect the caliper hardware—you want to confirm that the caliper slides are moving freely and aren't binding.",
